law.text:
A certificate of title is not required for:
A vehicle owned and used by the United States, unless it is registered in this State;
A new vehicle owned by a manufacturer or dealer and held for sale, even though incidentally moved on the highway or used for purposes of testing or demonstration or used as allowed under § 13-621 of this title;
A vehicle used by a manufacturer only for testing;
A vehicle owned by a nonresident of this State and not required by law to be registered in this State;
A vehicle regularly engaged in the interstate transportation of people or property and for which a currently effective certificate of title has been issued in another state;
A vehicle moved only by human or animal power;
A bicycle, except for a moped;
A vehicle in which interest has passed to a secured party on default of the owner;
Farm equipment;
Special mobile equipment;
A self-propelled invalid:
Wheelchair; or
Tricycle;
A trailer, other than a camping trailer, rated by the manufacturer as having a gross vehicle weight of 2,500 pounds or less; or
An off-highway recreational vehicle purchased before October 1, 2010.
